---
# =============================================================================
# LABORATORY EQUIPMENT / MACHINE MARKDOWN TEMPLATE
# Save new files as: content/_equipments/[unique-slug].md
# Note: Keep the filename and the "id" field below identical (use kebab-case).
# =============================================================================

# [REQUIRED] A unique identifier for the machine in kebab-case. 
# Matches the markdown filename (excluding .md) and the image folder name under public/images/labs/.
id: "equipment-slug-id"

# [REQUIRED] The display name of the equipment (e.g. "Analytical Balance").
name: "Name of the Equipment"

# [REQUIRED] The room or laboratory where the machine is located.
room: "Room XXX - [Name of Laboratory]"

# [REQUIRED] The category to group this equipment under in the UI explorer.
# Common Categories:
#   - "General Laboratory Equipment"
#   - "Analytical & Characterization Instruments"
#   - "Microfabrication & Cleanroom Systems"
#   - "Thermal Processing & Furnaces"
#   - "Sample Preparation & Processing"
#   - "Optical & Metrology Instruments"
category: "Category Name"

# [OPTIONAL] A brief 1-2 sentence description summarizing the main purpose/accuracy of the machine.
description: "Provides high-precision measurements and processing for advanced materials research and experimental training."

# [REQUIRED] List of image URLs representing the equipment. 
# Store actual image files under: public/images/labs/[equipment-slug-id]/
# Specify paths starting from the root (excluding 'public'):
images:
  - "/images/labs/equipment-slug-id/image-file-name.jpg"

# [OPTIONAL] A list of relevant PDF documents or operating procedures.
pdfs:
  - title: "Equipment Operating Procedure"
    url: "/Documents/MODULE CATALOGUE MSI.pdf"

# [OPTIONAL] A list of helpful links relevant to the equipment or laboratory overview.
links:
  - title: "VGU Laboratories Overview"
    url: "/laboratories-research"
    description: "Detailed overview of all equipment available in the VGU high-tech research facility"
---

## Integration in Academic & Research Programs

Provide a detailed description of how the equipment is integrated into the study program or ongoing research activities. 

### Key Guidelines for Body Content:
1. **Academic Connection**: Detail which master's program courses (e.g., Module name, Lab work, Practice sessions) actively utilize this machine.
2. **Student Projects**: Explain how students can interact with this machine for their group projects, research papers, or master's theses.
3. **Research Applications**: Explain what material properties, processing parameters, or manufacturing steps are analyzed using this equipment.
